title: Test
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Share of respondents, with a total of 6 data points.
Overall Share of respondents has increased over the Year
Share of respondents is gradually increasing from 65_years_and_over to 55_to_64_years, and lastly roughly constant from 55_to_64_years to All_adults.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 65_years_and_over and 55_to_64_years.
Max Share of respondents about 56.0 was recorded at Year 18_to_34_years
Min Share of respondents about 30.0 was recorded at Year 65_years_and_over
This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Share of respondents, with a total of 6 data points. The chart has 3 significant trends.
The longest trend is slightly increasing which exists from 45_to_54_years to 18_to_34_years.
Correspondingly, the next significant trend is slightly constant which exists from 65_years_and_over to 45_to_54_years.
But, the next significant trend is slightly decreasing which exists from 18_to_34_years to All_adults.
